    {
      "id": "1924750c-f3ba-80ff-8c88-d04998057681",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For personalized education services to work, it is often necessary that the systems are able to accurately predict the score a student will get on a given exercise. This is done via latent variables extractable from materials (e.g. knowledge concepts or exercise content). Thus, the paper makes multiple proposals:",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1924750c-f3ba-80ff-8c88-d04998057681",
        "parent": {
